<span id="freeTextContainer4113761452047000950">Not science fiction as the genre is commonly understood, but it still fits firmly within the overarching category. The greatest strength of the book is Smilla’s character. Høeg perfectly captures what it feels like to be an outsider: something that so many attempt and fail. I would go further and argue that <i>Smilla</i> did everything that <i>
  <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2429135.The_Girl_with_the_Dragon_Tattoo__Millennium___1_' title='The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo (Millennium, #1) by Stieg Larsson' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo</a>
</i> was trying to do . . . only better and about thirteen years earlier. What’s more, the film adaptation of <i>Smilla</i> really matches t</span>
  <span id="freeText4113761452047000950" style="display:none">Not science fiction as the genre is commonly understood, but it still fits firmly within the overarching category. The greatest strength of the book is Smilla’s character. Høeg perfectly captures what it feels like to be an outsider: something that so many attempt and fail. I would go further and argue that <i>Smilla</i> did everything that <i>
  <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2429135.The_Girl_with_the_Dragon_Tattoo__Millennium___1_" title="The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo (Millennium, #1) by Stieg Larsson" rel="nofollow noopener">The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo</a>
